pull.title: [travis-ci] Only run linters on Pull Requests
pull.body:
Linters should only be run on pull request builds. Once bad code style
has been merged into master, it's too late. Master and other branches
should not fail to build because of linter warnings.

issue.title: [trivial] remove trailing whitespace in streams.h
issue.body: Removes trailing whitespace added in #11221. I'm not sure how this passed the Travis linter for the PR, but it's causing some of my branches to fail on Travis.
